HTML Basics: Your Gateway to Web Development
item.description: HTML, which stands for HyperText Markup Language, is the backbone of the World Wide Web. It is the standard markup language used to create and structure web content. If you’ve ever viewed a webpage, you’ve interacted with HTML, whether you realized it or not. In this article, we will provide an introduction to HTML, exploring its history, basic structure, and fundamental elements. A Brief History of HTML HTML has come a long way since its inception in the early 1990s.
